<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B> <A NAME="ac17601_item_2.02._results_of___ac102020"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_ac17601_1"> </A> </B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2><B>  Item&nbsp;2.02.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Results of Operations and Financial Condition    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>On July&nbsp;24, 2015, Simon Property Group,&nbsp;Inc. issued a press release containing information on earnings for the quarter ended
June&nbsp;30, 2015 and other matters. A copy of the press release is furnished with this report as Exhibit&nbsp;99.1, and is incorporated by reference into this report.  </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="ac17601_item_7.01._regulation_fd_disclosure"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_ac17601_2"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>  Item&nbsp;7.01.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Regulation&nbsp;FD Disclosure    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Exhibit&nbsp;99.1 also includes supplemental financial and operating information for the quarter ended June&nbsp;30, 2015. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="ac17601_item_9.01._financial_statements_and_exhibits"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_ac17601_3"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>  Item&nbsp;9.01.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Financial Statements and Exhibits    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>

<TR VALIGN="BOTTOM">
<TH ALIGN="CENTER" style="font-family:arial;border-bottom:solid #000000 1.0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>Exhibit No. </B></FONT></TH>
<TH style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>&nbsp;</FONT></TH>
<TH ALIGN="CENTER" style="font-family:arial;border-bottom:solid #000000 1.0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>Description </B></FONT></TH>
</TR>
<TR VALIGN="TOP">
<TD ALIGN="CENTER" style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>99.1</FONT></TD>
<TD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Earnings Release dated July&nbsp;24, 2015 and supplemental information</FONT></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE></DIV>
<!-- end of user-specified TAGGED TABLE -->

 <P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
exhibit filed with this report contains measures of financial or operating performance that are not specifically defined by generally accepted accounting principles ("GAAP") in the United States,
including funds from operations ("FFO"), diluted FFO per share, comparable FFO per share, comparable earnings per share, funds available for distribution, net operating income ("NOI"), and comparable
property NOI. FFO and NOI are performance measures that are standard in the REIT business. We believe FFO and NOI provide investors with additional information concerning our operating performance and
a basis to compare our performance with the performance of other REITs. We also use these measures internally to monitor the operating performance of our portfolio. Our computation of these non-GAAP
measures may not be the same as similar measures reported by other REITs. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>These
non-GAAP financial measures should not be considered as alternatives to net income as a measure of our operating performance or to cash flows computed in accordance with GAAP as a measure of
liquidity nor are they indicative of cash flows from operating and financial activities. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Reconciliations
of each of these non-GAAP measures to the most-directly comparable GAAP measure are included in the exhibit. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
information in this report and the exhibit filed herewith is being furnished, not filed, for purposes of Section&nbsp;18 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended, and pursuant to
Items&nbsp;2.02 and 7.01 of Form&nbsp;8-K, will not be incorporated by reference into any filing under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended. </FONT></P>

 <P ALIGN="CENTER" style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="da17601_simon_property_group_reports_s__sim04296"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_da17601_2"> </A>
<BR></FONT><FONT SIZE=3><B>  SIMON PROPERTY GROUP REPORTS SECOND QUARTER 2015 RESULTS AND RAISES QUARTERLY DIVIDEND AND<BR>  FULL YEAR 2015 GUIDANCE  <BR>  </B></FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><B>INDIANAPOLIS, July&nbsp;24, 2015</B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>&nbsp;- Simon, a leading global retail real estate company, today reported results for the quarter ended
June&nbsp;30, 2015. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="da17601_results_for_the_quarter_1"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_da17601_3"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


RESULTS FOR THE QUARTER&nbsp;<SUP>1</SUP>    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>

<DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2> Funds from Operations ("FFO") was $955.4&nbsp;million, or $2.63 per diluted share, as compared to $783.8&nbsp;million, or $2.16
per diluted share, in the prior year period, a 21.8% increase. Included in the second quarter 2015 results is $80.2&nbsp;million, or $0.22 per diluted share, related to a gain upon sale of
marketable securities. The second quarter 2014 results include a net contribution of $0.05 per diluted share from the Washington Prime Group&nbsp;Inc. ("WPG") properties that were spun-off effective
May&nbsp;28, 2014. </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2> Net income attributable to common stockholders was $472.9&nbsp;million, or $1.52 per diluted share, as compared to
$406.6&nbsp;million, or $1.31 per diluted share, in the prior year period. </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2> Growth in comparable FFO per diluted share for the three months ended June&nbsp;30, 2015 was 14.2%. </FONT></DD></DL>

<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="da17601_results_for_the_six_months_1"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_da17601_4"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>



<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


RESULTS FOR THE SIX MONTHS&nbsp;<SUP>1</SUP>    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>

<DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2> Funds from Operations ("FFO") was $1.786&nbsp;billion, or $4.92 per diluted share, as compared to $1.649&nbsp;billion, or $4.54
per diluted share, in the prior year period. </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2> Net income attributable to common stockholders was $835.1&nbsp;million, or $2.69 per diluted share, as compared to
$748.2&nbsp;million, or $2.41 per diluted share, in the prior year period. </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2> Growth in comparable FFO per diluted share for the six months ended June&nbsp;30, 2015 was 10.8%.
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>1</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>For
a reconciliation of FFO and net income per diluted share on a comparable basis, please see Footnote&nbsp;H of the Footnotes to Unaudited Reconciliation
of Non-GAAP Financial Measures. </FONT></DD></DL>

EARNINGS RELEASE  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>"This
was an excellent quarter for Simon, with strong financial and operational performance," said David Simon, Chairman and CEO. "Our growing development and redevelopment opportunities position us
to continue to deliver strong results for our stockholders. Based upon our results to date and expectations for the remainder of 2015, we are once again raising our quarterly dividend and increasing
our full-year 2015 guidance." </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="da17601_comparable_property_net_operating_income"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_da17601_6"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


COMPARABLE PROPERTY NET OPERATING INCOME    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Comparable property NOI growth for the three months ended June&nbsp;30, 2015 was 3.6%. The growth for the six months ended
June&nbsp;30, 2015 was 3.5%. Comparable properties include U.S. Malls, Premium Outlets and The Mills. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="da17601_dividends"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_da17601_7"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


DIVIDENDS    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Today Simon's Board of Directors declared a quarterly common stock dividend of $1.55 per share. This is a 19.2% increase
year-over-year and an increase of $0.05 or 3.3% from the previous quarter. The dividend will be payable on August&nbsp;31, 2015 to stockholders of record on August&nbsp;17, 2015. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Simon's
Board of Directors also declared the quarterly dividend on its 8<SUP>3</SUP>/<SMALL>8</SMALL>% Series&nbsp;J Cumulative Redeemable Preferred Stock (NYSE: SPGPrJ) of $1.046875 per share, payable on
September&nbsp;30, 2015 to stockholders of record on September&nbsp;16, 2015. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="da17601_development_activity"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_da17601_8"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


DEVELOPMENT ACTIVITY    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>During the quarter, we completed a 140,000 square foot expansion of Las Vegas North Premium Outlets, one of the most productive and
well-known outlet centers in North America; and a 130,000 square foot expansion of Shisui Premium Outlets, a highly productive center in Shisui (Chiba), Japan. </FONT></P>
 <div style="padding:0pt;position:relative;width:100%;margin-top:24pt;">
<table width="100%" border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>

<tr valign="middle" style="height:24.0pt;background-color:#000000;">

<A NAME="page_da17601_1_4"> </A>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><A HREF="#bg17601a_main_toc">Table of Contents</A></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=5><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=5><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


EARNINGS RELEASE  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Construction
continues on three new Premium Outlets opening in 2015:</FONT></P>

<DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2> Gloucester Premium Outlets in Gloucester, New Jersey, serving the greater Philadelphia metropolitan area, is a 375,000 square foot
center scheduled to open in August. Simon owns a 50% interest in this project. </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2> Tucson Premium Outlets is a 366,000 square foot center scheduled to open in October. Simon owns 100% of this project. </FONT> <FONT SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2> Tampa Premium Outlets is a 441,000 square foot center scheduled to open in October. Simon owns 100% of this project. </FONT></DD></DL>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Construction
continues on other significant expansion projects including Roosevelt Field, Del Amo Fashion Center, King of Prussia, The Galleria in Houston, Woodbury Common Premium Outlets, San
Francisco Premium Outlets and Chicago Premium Outlets. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>At
quarter-end, redevelopment and expansion projects, including the addition of new anchors, were underway at 28 properties in the U.S. Simon's share of the costs of all development and redevelopment
projects under construction at quarter-end was approximately $2.3&nbsp;billion. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>During
the second quarter, construction started on two significant new development projects:</FONT></P>

<DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2> The Shops at Clearfork in Fort Worth, Texas&nbsp;- 590,000 square foot center projected to open in February 2017. Simon owns a 45%
interest in this project. </FONT><FONT SIZE=2>
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>&#149;</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2> A 355,000 square foot upscale outlet center located in Columbus, Ohio projected to open in June 2016. Simon owns a 50% interest in
this project. </FONT></DD></DL>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>We
entered into a partnership to jointly develop the 500,000 square foot retail component to Brickell City Centre in Miami, Florida, projected to open in September 2016. Simon owns a 25% interest in
this project. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>In
addition, Vancouver Designer Outlet in Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada opened on July&nbsp;9<SUP>th</SUP>. The center serves the greater Vancouver metropolitan market with 242,000 square
feet of high-quality, name brand stores. Simon owns a 45% interest in this center. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="da17601_joint_venture_transaction"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_da17601_9"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


JOINT VENTURE TRANSACTION    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>During the second quarter, we created a joint venture with Sears Holdings Corporation that includes 10 Sears stores located at our
malls. Sears Holdings subsequently sold its interest in the joint venture to Seritage Growth Properties. Sears Holdings is leasing and continues to operate the existing stores at the properties and
the joint venture will have the ability to create additional value through re-developing the contributed properties and re-leasing space at each property to third-party tenants. In July, we purchased
1,125,760 Seritage Growth Properties common shares at $29.58 per share. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>In
addition to the joint venture, we separately acquired a Sears store at the La Plaza Mall in McAllen, Texas. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="da17601_financing_activity"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_da17601_10"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


FINANCING ACTIVITY    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The Company was active in the secured debt markets in the first half of the year continuing to lower our effective borrowing costs.
We closed on seven new loans totaling approximately $2.4&nbsp;billion, or the non-U.S. dollar equivalent thereof, of which SPG's share is $1.2&nbsp;billion. The weighted average interest rate on
these loans is 2.9% and term is 8.0&nbsp;years. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=5><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=5><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


EARNINGS RELEASE  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>As
of June&nbsp;30, 2015, Simon had over $5.5&nbsp;billion of liquidity consisting of cash on hand, including its share of joint venture cash, and its available revolving credit facility capacity. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="da17601_common_stock_repurchase_program"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_da17601_11"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


COMMON STOCK REPURCHASE PROGRAM    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>On April&nbsp;2<SUP>nd</SUP>, the Company announced that its Board of Directors authorized a common stock repurchase program.
Under the program, the Company may purchase up to $2&nbsp;billion of its common stock over the next 24&nbsp;months as market conditions warrant. The shares may be purchased in the open market or
in privately negotiated transactions. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>During
the quarter ended June&nbsp;30, 2015, the Company invested $505.7&nbsp;million for the purchase of 1,903,340 shares of its common stock and 944,359 limited partnership units. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="da17601_2015_guidance"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_da17601_12"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


2015 GUIDANCE    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Today, the Company is raising both the low and high ends of its previously provided full year 2015&nbsp;FFO range and currently
estimates a range of $10.02 to $10.07 per diluted share for the year ending December&nbsp;31, 2015, with net income to be within a range of $5.47 to $5.52 per diluted share. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
following table provides the reconciliation for the expected range of estimated net income available to common stockholders per diluted share to estimated FFO per diluted share: </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


For the year ending December&nbsp;31, 2015 </FONT></P>

CONFERENCE CALL    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Simon will hold a conference call to discuss the quarterly financial results today at 11:00&nbsp;a.m. Eastern Time, Friday,
July&nbsp;24, 2015. A live webcast of the conference call will be accessible in listen-only mode at investors.simon.com. An audio replay of the conference call will be available until
July&nbsp;31, 2015. To access the audio replay, dial 1-888-286-8010 (international 617-801-6888) passcode 52068250. </FONT></P>

furnished to the SEC in a current report on Form&nbsp;8-K. </FONT></P>

EARNINGS RELEASE  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>We
routinely post important information online at our investor relations website, investors.simon.com. We use this website, press releases, SEC filings, quarterly conference calls, presentations and
webcasts to disclose material, non-public information in accordance with Regulation&nbsp;FD. We encourage members of the investment community to monitor these distribution channels for material
disclosures. Any information accessed through our website is not incorporated by reference into, and is not a part of, this document. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="da17601_non-gaap_financial_measures"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_da17601_15"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


NON-GAAP FINANCIAL MEASURES    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>This press release includes FFO, FFO per share, comparable FFO per share, comparable earnings per share and comparable property net
operating income growth, which are financial performance measures not defined by generally accepted accounting principles in the United States ("GAAP"). Reconciliations of these non-GAAP financial
measures to the most directly comparable GAAP measures are included in this press release and in
Simon's supplemental information for the quarter. FFO and comparable property net operating income growth are financial performance measures widely used in the REIT industry. Our definitions of these
non-GAAP measures may not be the same as similar measures reported by other REITs. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="da17601_forward-looking_statements"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_da17601_16"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


FORWARD-LOOKING STATEMENTS    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Certain statements made in this press release may be deemed "forward-looking statements" within the meaning of the Private Securities
Litigation Reform Act of 1995. Although the Company believes the expectations reflected in any forward-looking statements are based on reasonable assumptions, the Company can give no assurance that
its expectations will be attained, and it is possible that actual results may differ materially from those indicated by these forward-looking statements due to a variety of risks, uncertainties and
other factors. Such factors include, but are not limited to: the Company's ability to meet debt service requirements, the availability and terms of financing, changes in the Company's credit rating,
changes in market rates of interest and foreign exchange rates for foreign currencies, changes in value of investments in foreign entities, the ability to hedge interest rate and currency risk, risks
associated with the acquisition, development, expansion, leasing and management of properties, general risks related to retail real estate, the liquidity of real estate investments, environmental
liabilities, international, national, regional and local economic conditions, changes in market rental rates, security breaches that could compromise our information technology or infrastructure or
personally identifiable data of customers of our retail properties, trends in the retail industry, relationships with anchor tenants, the inability to collect rent due to the bankruptcy or insolvency
of tenants or otherwise, risks relating to joint venture properties, the intensely competitive market environment in the retail industry, costs of common area maintenance, risks related to
international activities, insurance costs and coverage, the loss of key management personnel, terrorist activities, changes in economic and market conditions and maintenance of our status as a real
estate investment trust. The Company discusses these and other risks and uncertainties under the heading "Risk Factors" in our annual and quarterly reports filed with the SEC. The Company undertakes
no duty or obligation to update or revise these forward-looking statements, whether as a result of new information, future developments, or otherwise unless required by law. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="da17601_about_simon"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_da17601_17"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>



<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


ABOUT SIMON    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Simon is a global leader in retail real estate ownership, management and development and a S&amp;P100 company (Simon Property Group,
NYSE:SPG). Our industry-leading retail properties and investments across North America, Europe and Asia provide shopping experiences for millions of consumers every day and generate billions in annual
retail sales. For more information, visit simon.com. </FONT></P>

<A NAME="toc_fa17601_1"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=5><B>

 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=5><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


EARNINGS RELEASE    <BR>  </B></FONT></P>

<P ALIGN="CENTER" style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="fa17601_simon_property_group,_inc._and__sim04435"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_fa17601_2"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=3><B>  Simon Property Group,&nbsp;Inc. and Subsidiaries<BR>  </B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2><I>Footnotes to Unaudited Reconciliation of Non-GAAP Financial Measures    <BR>    </I></FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="fa17601_notes_"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_fa17601_3"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


Notes:    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>

<DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(A)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Excess
investment represents the unamortized difference of our investment over equity in the underlying net assets of the related partnerships and joint
ventures shown therein. The Company generally amortizes excess investment over the life of the related properties.
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(B)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
Unaudited Joint Venture Statements of Operations do not include any operations or our share of net income or excess investment amortization related to
our investment in Kl&eacute;pierre. Amounts included in Footnotes D below exclude our share of related activity for our investment in Kl&eacute;pierre. For further information,
reference should be made to financial information in Kl&eacute;pierre's public filings and additional discussion and analysis in our Form&nbsp;10-Q.
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(C)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>This
report contains measures of financial or operating performance that are not specifically defined by GAAP, including FFO, FFO per share, comparable FFO
per share and comparable EPS. FFO is a performance measure that is standard in the REIT business. We believe FFO provides investors with additional information concerning our operating performance and
a basis to compare our performance with those of other REITs. We also use these measures internally to monitor the operating performance of our portfolio. Our computation of these non-GAAP measures
may not be the same as similar measures reported by other REITs.  </FONT>
<BR>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>We
determine FFO based upon the definition set forth by the National Association of Real Estate Investment Trusts ("NAREIT"). We determine FFO to be our share of consolidated net income computed in
accordance with GAAP, excluding real estate related depreciation and amortization, excluding gains and losses from extraordinary items, excluding gains and losses from the sales or disposals of, or
any impairment charges related to, previously depreciated retail operating properties, plus the allocable portion of FFO of unconsolidated joint ventures based upon economic ownership interest, and
all determined on a consistent basis in accordance with GAAP.  </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>We
have adopted NAREIT's clarification of the definition of FFO that requires it to include the effects of nonrecurring items not classified as extraordinary, cumulative effect of accounting changes,
or a gain or loss resulting from the sale or disposal of, or any impairment charges relating to, previously depreciated retail operating properties. We include in FFO gains and losses realized from
the sale of land, outlot buildings, marketable and non-marketable securities, and investment holdings of non-retail real estate. However, you should understand that FFO does not represent cash flow
from operations as defined by GAAP, should not be considered as an alternative to net income determined in accordance with GAAP as a measure of operating performance, and is not an alternative to cash
flows as a measure of liquidity.  </FONT></P>

</DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(D)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Includes
our share of:
<BR><BR></FONT>
<DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>-</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Gains
on land sales of $3.6&nbsp;million and $5.6&nbsp;million for the three months ended June&nbsp;30, 2015 and 2014, respectively, and
$3.7&nbsp;million and $12.4&nbsp;million for the six months ended June&nbsp;30, 2015 and 2014, respectively.
<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>-</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Straight-line
adjustments to minimum rent of $16.8&nbsp;million and $13.3&nbsp;million for the three months ended June&nbsp;30, 2015 and 2014,
respectively (including $0.2&nbsp;million related to WPG in 2014), and $33.2&nbsp;million and $27.3&nbsp;million for the six months ended June&nbsp;30, 2015 and 2014, respectively (including
$0.3&nbsp;million related to WPG in 2014). </FONT></DD></DL>
</DD></DL>

<BR><BR></FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(H)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Reconciliation
of reported earnings per share to comparable earnings per share and FFO per share to comparable FFO per share: </FONT></DD></DL>
 <DIV style="padding:0pt;position:relative;width:60%;margin-left:20%;">
<p style="font-family:arial;"></FONT></P>

and six month periods ended June&nbsp;30, 2014 include a gain on disposition of $0.37 per diluted share related to Kl&eacute;pierre's sale
of a portfolio of 126 retail galleries. </FONT></DD></DL>

<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="fc17601_overview"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_fc17601_1"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=5><B>

 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=5><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


<A NAME="OVERVIEW"></A>OVERVIEW    <BR>  </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="fc17601_the_company"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_fc17601_2"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>



<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


THE COMPANY    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Simon Property Group,&nbsp;Inc. (NYSE:SPG) is a self-administered and self-managed real estate investment trust ("REIT"). Simon
Property Group,&nbsp;L.P., or the Operating Partnership, is our majority-owned partnership subsidiary that owns all of our real estate properties and other assets. In this package, the terms Simon,
we, our, or the Company refer to Simon Property Group,&nbsp;Inc., the Operating Partnership, and its subsidiaries. We are engaged primarily in the ownership, development and management of retail
real estate properties including Malls, Premium Outlets&reg;, The Mills&reg;, and International Properties. At June&nbsp;30, 2015, we owned or had an interest in 228 properties
comprising 189&nbsp;million square feet in North America, Asia and Europe. Additionally, at June&nbsp;30, 2015, we had an 20.3% ownership interest in Kl&eacute;pierre, a publicly traded,
Paris-based real estate company, which owns shopping centers in 16&nbsp;European countries. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>This
package was prepared to provide operational and balance sheet information as of June&nbsp;30, 2015, for the Company and the Operating Partnership. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>On
May&nbsp;28, 2014, we completed the spin-off of 98 smaller malls and community centers to Washington Prime Group&nbsp;Inc. (WPG), now doing business as WP GLIMCHER. Results from the properties
transferred to WPG (WPG properties) are included in our financial information as discontinued operations through May&nbsp;28, 2014. </FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Certain
statements made in this Supplemental Package may be deemed "forward-looking statements" within the meaning of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995. Although we believe the
expectations reflected in any forward-looking statements are based on reasonable assumptions, we can give no assurance that our expectations will be attained, and it is possible that actual results
may differ materially from those indicated by these forward-looking statements due to a variety of risks, uncertainties and other factors. Such factors include, but are not limited to: our ability to
meet debt service requirements, the availability and terms of financing, changes in our credit rating, changes in market rates of interest and foreign exchange rates for foreign currencies, changes in
value of investments in foreign entities, the ability to hedge interest rate and currency risk, risks associated with the acquisition, development, expansion, leasing and management of properties,
general risks related to retail real estate, the liquidity of real estate investments, environmental liabilities, international, national, regional and local economic climates, changes in market
rental rates, security breaches that could compromise our information technology or infrastructure or personally identifiable data of customers of our retail properties, trends in the retail industry,
relationships with anchor tenants, the inability to collect rent due to the bankruptcy or insolvency of tenants or otherwise, risks relating to joint venture properties, costs of common area
maintenance, intensely competitive market environment in the retail industry, risks related to international activities, insurance costs and coverage, terrorist activities, changes in economic and
market conditions, the loss of key management personnel and maintenance of our status as a real estate investment trust.
We discuss these and other risks and uncertainties under the heading "Risk Factors" in our annual and quarterly periodic reports filed with the SEC. We may update that discussion in our periodic
reports, but except as required by law, otherwise we undertake no duty or obligation to update or revise these forward-looking statements, whether as a result of new information, future developments,
or otherwise. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Any
questions, comments or suggestions regarding this Supplemental Information should be directed to Tom Ward, Vice President of Investor Relations (tom.ward@simon.com or 317.685.7330). </FONT></P>

 <P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="fc17601_senior_unsecured_debt_covenants_(1)"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_fc17601_6"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>

 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


SENIOR UNSECURED DEBT COVENANTS <SUP>(1)</SUP>    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>
 <DIV style="padding:0pt;position:relative;width:54%;margin-left:10%;">
<p style="font-family:arial;"></FONT></P>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TABLEWIDTH,"150%" -->

<!-- User-specified TAGGED TABLE -->

<TD WIDTH="12pt" style="font-family:arial;"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" style="font-family:arial;"><FONT  style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="RIGHT" VALIGN="BOTTOM" style="font-family:arial;"><FONT  style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;"><B> 100.00%</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" style="font-family:arial;"><FONT  style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE></DIV>
<!-- end of user-specified TAGGED TABLE -->
 </DIV>
<DIV style="padding:0pt;position:relative;text-align:left;margin-left:0%;">
 <DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-9pt;'><FONT  style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">(1)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT  style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">Represents
our venture partners' share of operations from consolidated properties.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-9pt;'><FONT  style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">(2)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT  style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">Our
Total Share of income from unconsolidated entities represents our share of net results related to our investment in Kl&eacute;pierre. </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-9pt;'><FONT  style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">(3)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT  style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">Represents
limited partners' interest in the Operating Partnership. </FONT></DD></DL>

 <P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="fi17601_basis_of_presentation_"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_fi17601_2"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


BASIS OF PRESENTATION:    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>


<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT  style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">We present balance sheet and income statement data on a pro-rata basis reflecting our
proportionate economic ownership of each asset in our portfolio. The consolidated amounts shown are prepared on a consistent basis with our consolidated financial statements. Our Share of Joint
Ventures column was derived on a property-by-property basis by applying the same joint venture ownership percentage interests used to arrive at our share of net income during the period and applying
them to all financial statement line items of each property. A similar calculation was performed for noncontrolling interests. </FONT></P>
 <div style="padding:0pt;position:relative;width:100%;margin-top:24pt;">

 </DIV>
 <P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT  style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">This report contains measures of financial or operating performance that are not specifically defined by generally accepted accounting principles (GAAP) in the
United States, including FFO, diluted FFO per share, funds available for distribution, net operating income (NOI), and comparable property NOI. FFO and NOI are performance measures that are standard
in the REIT business. We believe FFO and NOI provide investors with additional information concerning our operating performance and a basis to compare our performance with the performance of other
REITs. We also use these measures internally to monitor the operating performance of our portfolio. Our computation of these non-GAAP measures may not be the same as similar measures reported by other
REITs. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;"><FONT  style="font-size:8pt;line-height:9pt;">The non-GAAP financial measures used in this report should not be considered as alternatives to net income as a measure
of our operating performance or to cash flows computed in accordance with GAAP as a measure of liquidity nor are they indicative of cash flows from operating and financial activities. Reconciliations
of other non-GAAP measures used in this report to the most-directly comparable GAAP measure are included in the tables on pages 18-19, 22 and 23 and in the Earnings Release for the latest period. </FONT></P>

<P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="fq17601_u.s._malls_and_premium__fq102078"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_fq17601_1"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=5><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=5><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


U.S. MALLS AND PREMIUM OUTLETS OPERATING INFORMATION  <SUP>(1)</SUP>    <BR>  </B></FONT></P>

<div
style="position:relative;float:left;width:47%;clear:left;">

<div style="width:100%;clear:both;"></div>

<DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(1)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Excludes
WPG properties and all prior periods have been restated.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(2)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Ending
Occupancy is the percentage of total owned square footage (GLA) which is leased as of the last day of the reporting period. We include all company
owned space except for mall anchors, mall majors, mall freestanding and mall outlots in the calculation.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(3)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Total
Sales PSF is defined as total sales of the tenants open and operating in the center during the reporting period divided by the associated company
owned and occupied GLA on a trailing 12-month basis. Includes tenant sales activity for all months a tenant is open within the trailing 12-month period. In accordance with the standard definition of
sales for regional malls adopted by the International Council of Shopping Centers, only stores with less than 10,000 square feet are included for malls. All company owned space is included for Premium
Outlets.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(4)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Base
Minimum Rent PSF is the average base minimum rent charge in effect for the reporting period for all tenants that would qualify to be included in Ending
Occupancy as defined above.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(5)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Releasing
Spread is a "same space" measure that compares opening and closing rates on individual spaces, including spaces greater than 10,000 square feet.
The Opening Rate is the average of the initial cash Total Rent PSF for spaces leased during the trailing 12-month period, and includes new leases and existing tenant renewals, amendments and
relocations (including expansions and downsizings). The Closing Rate is the average of the final cash Total Rent PSF as of the month the tenant terminates or closes. Total Rent PSF includes Base
Minimum Rent, common area maintenance (CAM) and base percentage rent. It includes leasing activity on all spaces occupied by tenants that would qualify to be included in Ending Occupancy as defined
above as long as the opening and closing dates are within 24&nbsp;months of one another.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(6)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Occupancy
Cost as a Percentage of Sales is the trailing 12-month Base Minimum Rent, plus all applicable ancillary charges, plus overage rent, if applicable
(based on last 12&nbsp;months of sales), divided by the trailing 12-month Total Sales PSF for the same tenants. </FONT></DD></DL>
 <div style="padding:0pt;position:relative;width:100%;margin-top:24pt;">

 <DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(1)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Does
not consider the impact of renewal options that may be contained in leases.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(2)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Annual
rental revenues represent domestic 2014 consolidated and joint venture combined base rental revenue excluding WPG properties. </FONT></DD></DL>

 <P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


TOP ANCHORS  </B></FONT><FONT SIZE=2>(sorted by percentage of total square footage in U.S. properties) <SUP>(1)</SUP>    <BR></FONT></P>
 <DIV style="padding:0pt;position:relative;width:95%;margin-left:4%;">
<p style="font-family:arial;"></FONT></P>

<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TABLEWIDTH,"100%" -->

<!-- User-specified TAGGED TABLE -->
<DIV ALIGN="CENTER"><TABLE width="100%"  BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0>
<TR><!-- TABLE COLUMN WIDTHS SET -->

 <DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(1)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Expenditures
included in the pool of expenses allocated to tenants as CAM.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(2)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Agrees
with the line item "Capital expenditures" on the Combined Statements of Cash Flows for the consolidated properties. No statement of cash flows is
prepared for the joint venture properties; however, the above reconciliation was completed in the same manner as the reconciliation for the consolidated properties. </FONT></DD></DL>

 <P style="font-family:arial;;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;"><FONT SIZE=2><A
NAME="gc17601_notes_"> </A>
<A NAME="toc_gc17601_2"> </A></FONT> <FONT SIZE=2><B>


<!-- COMMAND=ADD_TXTHEX,"PMS322" -->


</B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=2><B>



<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


Notes:    <BR>    </B></FONT></P>

<DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(1)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Represents
projects under construction; new development and redevelopment projects with budgeted gross costs in excess of $5&nbsp;million; and anchor/big
box/restaurant additions with budgeted gross costs in excess of $2&nbsp;million. Includes both domestic and international properties.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(2)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Projected
Gross Cost includes soft costs such as architecture and engineering fees, tenant costs (allowances/leasing commissions), development, legal and
other fees, marketing costs, cost of capital, and other related costs.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(3)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Projected
Net Cost includes cost recoveries such as land sales, tenant reimbursements, Tax Increment Financing (TIF), CAM, and other such recoveries. </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(4)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Costs
and returns are based upon current budget assumptions; actual costs may vary. </FONT></DD></DL>

 </B></FONT><FONT COLOR="#006362" SIZE=5><B>


<!-- COMMAND=STYLE_ADDED,"margin-left:0pt;text-indent:-0pt;" -->


PROPERTY AND DEBT INFORMATION<BR>  </B></FONT><FONT SIZE=3>As of June&nbsp;30, 2015 </FONT></P>

<DL compact>
<DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2><B>FOOTNOTES:</B></FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>&#160; </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(1)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Variable
rate debt interest rates are based on the following base rates as of June&nbsp;30, 2015: 1M LIBOR at .19%; 1M EUR LIBOR at -.06%; 1M EURIBOR at
-.06%; 3M EURIBOR at -.01%; 6M EURIBOR at .05%; 1M YEN LIBOR at .06%; 6M YEN LIBOR at .14%; 1M CDOR at .99%; KLIBOR at 3.39% and 91 Day Korean CD rate at 1.65%.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(2)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Unencumbered
asset.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(3)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>This
property is managed by a third party.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(4)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
Operating Partnership's direct and indirect interests in some joint venture properties are subject to preferences on distributions and/or capital
allocation in favor of other partners or the Operating Partnership.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(5)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Amounts
shown in USD equivalent; GBP equivalent is 40.0&nbsp;million.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(6)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>These
three properties are secured by cross-collateralized and cross-defaulted mortgages.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(7)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
Operating Partnership receives substantially all the economic benefit of the property due to a preference or advance.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(8)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Includes
applicable extensions available at our option.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(9)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>These
three properties are secured by cross-collateralized and cross-defaulted mortgages.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(10)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>The
Operating Partnership owns a mortgage note that encumbers Pheasant Lane Mall that entitles it to 100% of the economics of this property. </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(11)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Through
an interest rate swap agreement, interest is essentially fixed at the all-in-rate presented.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(12)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Amount
shown in USD equivalent; Euro equivalent is 172.0&nbsp;million.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(13)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Loan
refinanced after June 30, 2015.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(14)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>These
three properties are secured by cross-collateralized and cross-defaulted mortgages.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(15)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>These
three properties are secured by cross-collateralized and cross-defaulted mortgages.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(16)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>These
ten properties (which includes Florida Keys Outlet Center, Huntley Outlet Center and Naples Outlet Center) are secured by cross-collateralized and
cross-defaulted mortgages.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(17)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>These
two properties are secured by cross-collateralized and cross-defaulted mortgages.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(18)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Also
represents our share of Total Unsecured Indebtedness.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(19)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Amounts
shown in USD equivalent; balance includes borrowings on multi-currency tranche of Yen 22.3&nbsp;billion.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(20)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Amounts
shown in USD equivalent; Euro equivalent is 394.5&nbsp;million.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(21)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Consists
of five encumbered properties with interest rates ranging from 3.09% to 5.62% and maturities between 2016 and 2020.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(22)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Amount
shown in USD equivalent; Euro equivalent is 750.0&nbsp;million.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(23)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Includes
five properties with interest rates ranging from 4.50% to 7.32% and maturities between 2015 and 2023.  </FONT></DD><DT style='font-family:arial;margin-bottom:-11pt;'><FONT SIZE=2>(24)</FONT></DT><DD style="font-family:arial;"><FONT SIZE=2>Includes
office space of 1,889,925 square feet including the following centers with more than 20,000 square feet of office space: </FONT></DD></DL>
